<paragraph blockId="11.[132,775,511,562]" pageId="11" pageNumber="416">
<typeStatus box="[132,181,512,535]" pageId="11" pageNumber="416">TYPE</typeStatus>
SPECIES. — 
<taxonomicName authority="Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1893" authorityName="Brunner von Wattenwyl" authorityYear="1893" box="[304,775,511,535]" class="Insecta" family="Haglotettigoniidae" genus="Amusurgus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvus">
<emphasis box="[304,468,511,535]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="416">Amusurgus fulvus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="BRUNNER VON WATTENWYL K." box="[475,775,511,535]" pageId="11" pageNumber="416" refId="ref33718" refString="BRUNNER VON WATTENWYL K. 1893. - Revision du systeme des Orthopteres et description des especes rapportees par M. Fea de Birmanie. Tip. del R. Instituto Sordo-Muti, Genova, 230 p., 6 pls." type="book" year="1893">Brunner von Wattenwyl, 1893</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by monotypy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[132,775,585,636]" pageId="11" pageNumber="416">
ILLUSTRATIONS. — Habitus: 
<figureCitation box="[430,507,585,609]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="12.[133,144,1985,2003]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,221,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-74@12.[698,1267,787,1361]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIG. 3. — New Caledonian Trigonidiinae (Trigonidiidae): A, Anaxipha sp., male, from Col d’Amieu; B, Amusurgus sp., from Lifou (Loyalty Islands); C, Metioche sp., from the Seychelles (Photo SH); D, Trigonidomorpha sp. from Mauritius (Photo SH). Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4578286" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4578286/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="416">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D." box="[521,768,585,609]" pageId="11" pageNumber="416" pagination="1 - 477" refId="ref35794" refString="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D. 1983. - Australian crickets. Monographs of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 22: 1 - 477." type="journal article" year="1983">Otte &amp; Alexander 1983</bibRefCitation>
: figs 149, 150. Male genitalia: 
<bibRefCitation author="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D." box="[423,657,612,636]" pageId="11" pageNumber="416" pagination="1 - 477" refId="ref35794" refString="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D. 1983. - Australian crickets. Monographs of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 22: 1 - 477." type="journal article" year="1983">Otte &amp; Alexander 1983</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 152.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="416" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[131,777,659,1054]" pageId="11" pageNumber="416">
EMENDED DIAGNOSIS. — After 
<bibRefCitation author="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D." box="[439,689,659,683]" pageId="11" pageNumber="416" pagination="1 - 477" refId="ref35794" refString="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D. 1983. - Australian crickets. Monographs of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 22: 1 - 477." type="journal article" year="1983">Otte &amp; Alexander (1983)</bibRefCitation>
for 
<collectingCountry name="Australia" pageId="11" pageNumber="416">Australia</collectingCountry>
and material from 
<collectingCountry box="[359,507,686,710]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="11" pageNumber="416">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
preserved in MNHN. Head dorsum not flat between eyes. TI with a wide inner tympanum; outer tympanum grooved. FWs hairy; flat in lateral view. HWs well developed but shorter than FWs. TIII with three pairs of long and thin alternate subapical spurs; only five relatively short apical spurs, ventral inner spur lacking.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[131,777,659,1054]" pageId="11" pageNumber="416">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[132,189,845,869]" pageId="11" pageNumber="416">Male.</emphasis>
Dorsal gland on abdomen. No stridulatory device. Subgenital plate large, distal margin bisinuate. Male genitalia: distal pseudepiphallic median lobes well developed and divergent; lateral lobes dejected latero-ventrally, as long or longer than median lobes (see 
<bibRefCitation author="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D." box="[133,360,950,974]" pageId="11" pageNumber="416" pagination="1 - 477" refId="ref35794" refString="OTTE D. &amp; ALEXANDER R. D. 1983. - Australian crickets. Monographs of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia 22: 1 - 477." type="journal article" year="1983">Otte &amp; Alexander 1983</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 152); pseudepiphallic parameres small.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[131,777,659,1054]" pageId="11" pageNumber="416">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[132,211,977,1001]" pageId="11" pageNumber="416">Female.</emphasis>
FWs developed as in males. Ovipositor: distal margins of dorsal and ventral valves feebly crenulated (see Otte &amp; Alexan- der 1983: fig. 153).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="416" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[130,775,1077,1154]" pageId="11" pageNumber="416">
DISTRIBUTION. — Mostly diversified in South 
<collectingCountry box="[567,652,1077,1101]" name="China" pageId="11" pageNumber="416">East Asia</collectingCountry>
and Oceania (see 
<bibRefCitation author="EADES D. C. &amp; OTTE D. &amp; CIGLIANO M. M. &amp; BRAUN H." box="[176,344,1104,1128]" pageId="11" pageNumber="416" refId="ref34935" refString="EADES D. C., OTTE D., CIGLIANO M. M. &amp; BRAUN H. 2016. - Orthoptera species file. Version 5.0 / 5.0 [7. VI. 2016] http: // orthoptera. speciesfile. org" type="url" year="2016">
Eades 
<emphasis box="[239,287,1104,1128]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="416">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
); reported here for the first time from 
<collectingCountry name="New Caledonia" pageId="11" pageNumber="416">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[244,395,1130,1154]" country="New Caledonia" name="Province des Iles" pageId="11" pageNumber="416">Loyalty islands</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
